doc.after: The airframe of an aircraft is its mechanical structure It is typically considered to include fuselage wings and undercarriage and exclude the propulsion system Airframe design is a field of aerospace engineering that combines aerodynamics materials technology and manufacturing methods to achieve balances of performance reliability and cost 1
